'''''Canarium apertum''''' is a tree in the family [[Burseraceae]]. The [[specific name (botany)|specific epithet]] ''{{lang|la|[[:wikt:apertus|apertum]]}}'' is from the [[Latin]] meaning "open", referring to the [[:wikt:basal|basal]] openings between petals.<ref name=TFSS/>

==Description==
''Canarium apertum'' grows up to {{convert|40|m|-1}} tall with a trunk diameter of up to {{convert|80|cm|0}}. The scaly bark is grey-brown. The flowers are yellow-brown. The fruits are [[:wikt:ovoid|ovoid]] and measure up to {{convert|5|cm|in|0|abbr=on}} long.<ref name=TFSS/>

==Distribution and habitat==
''Canarium apertum'' grows naturally in [[Sumatra]], [[Peninsular Malaysia]] and [[Borneo]]. Its habitat is lowland mixed [[dipterocarp]] forest from sea-level to {{convert|500|m|-2}} altitude.<ref name=TFSS/>

